Theory:
An array is a collection of elements of the same data type stored in contiguous memory locations. Arrays allow us to store multiple values under a single variable name and access them using an index. In this experiment, we learn how to traverse an array using a for loop and find the largest element by comparing each element with a variable storing the current maximum value.
*/

public class Exp5c 
{
    public static void main(String[] args) 
    {
        // Declare and initialize an array of integers
        int[] arr = { 20, 40, 60, 80 };

        // Assume the first element is the largest initially
        int max = arr[0];

        // Loop through the array to compare each element
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) 
        {
            // If current element is greater than max, update max
            if (arr[i] > max) 
            {
                max = arr[i];
            }
        }

        // Print the largest element found in the array
        System.out.println("Largest element of array is : " + max);
    }
}
